XML_RESOURCE.RESOURCE: Manual Fuel Control Valve Adjustment Manual Fuel Control Valve Adjustment will allow the adjustment of the Fuel Control Valve Position to verify functionality while the engine is running Parameter Value Units Before starting the test, troubleshoot all active fault codes. Make the desired adjustment. These adjustments will be made once per second. When the adjustment is made the tool will state in the Status box when the next adjustment can be made. Select Stop to stop the test. Manual Fuel Valve Position Original Value Status Instructions: The requested adjustment is outside the allowable range, please make a new adjustment. Restore INSITE has restored the original value for Manual Fuel Control Valve Adjustment. Ready for the next adjustment Monitors Adjustments Cummins INSITE ECM Communication Lost.
